title: For Sale:  Harrington & Richardson "Reising Model 65"
postcontent: Harrington & Richardson "Reising Model 65" semi-automatic rifle. Chambered for the .22 Long Rifle, the Model 65 was designed by Eugene Reising during WWII at the request of the U.S. Government for a semi-automatic .22 caliber training rifle which would better simulate the function of the M1 Garand. It features a standard blow-back type semi-automatic action and a detachable 10-shot magazine. The action is cocked and the first round chambered via a charging lever that is accessed via a port in the underside of the forend. The medium weight barrel measures 23-inches in length and the front sight has protective ears. Rear sighting is accomplished by a Redfield reciever sight.
